wikipedia_page.main: James Burt (28 October 1792 – 4 September 1858) was an English amateur cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1825 to 1832.  He was mainly associated with Hampshire and Marylebone Cricket Club (MCC), of which he was a member.  He made 13 known appearances in first-class matches, including 3 for The Bs from 1828 to 1832.
